      "component": "Maladaptive Strategies",
      "item": "Avoid Police: Police",
      "explanation": "Avoiding police as a trigger is inconsistent with the absence of police-related triggers in the Triggers component. The triggers listed (moral violation, stress, event-related people) don't include police, yet police avoidance is a primary maladaptive strategy, creating a cross-node inconsistency in the trauma context."
    },
    {
      "component": "Threat",
      "item": "Risky Behavior: Taking too many risks or doing things that could cause you harm",
      "explanation": "Risky behavior contradicts the constant vigilance and carefulness expressed in Negative Appraisals ('I have to be especially careful'). These represent opposing behavioral tendencies - hypervigilant caution versus risk-taking - that are clinically implausible to coexist as primary symptoms."
    }
